Preconditions:
The input matrix `mat` is not null.
The input matrix `mat` is a 2D array of integers.
The input matrix `mat` has at least one row and one column.
The input target value `target` is an integer.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value representing the minimum absolute difference.
The returned value is the minimum absolute difference between the sum of any subset of elements from each row of the matrix `mat` and the target value `target`.